---
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
import { SHOW_DRAFTS } from 'astro:env/server';
import PostList from '../components/PostList.astro';
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { isVisible, sortByPubDateDesc } from '../lib/posts';
import { profilePageJsonLd } from '../lib/seo';

const recent = sortByPubDateDesc(
  await getCollection('posts', ({ data }) => isVisible(data, SHOW_DRAFTS)),
).slice(0, 3);

const site = Astro.site?.href ?? 'https://davidlowelarsson.com';
---

<Base title="David Lowe Larsson" jsonLd={profilePageJsonLd(site)}>
  <h1>David Lowe Larsson</h1>
  <p>
    This is a notebook about how software gets made. I write
    <a href="/category/essay/">essays</a> — sometimes about how things were fifteen years ago,
    sometimes about where I think they're going — <a href="/category/til/">quick notes</a>
    captured the day I learn something, and <a href="/category/experiment/">experiments</a> from
    the home lab or other learnings. Now and then the old visual effects and 3D work shows up too, or some new 3D
    printing, mostly because it's fun to remember and fun to build.
  </p>
  <p>
    I started in 3D art and visual effects — Maya, ZBrush, After Effects — modeling, texturing,
    animating, and writing shaders and exporters because the tools were never quite what I
    needed. Somewhere along the way, building the tools became the craft. These days I do
    technical leadership, DevSecOps, and platform engineering: Kubernetes, GitOps, automating
    things until they no longer need me ... but there is always something more to automate 😅.
  </p>
  <p>
    Away from the keyboard there's a wife and two daughters, I enjoy sailing and dream about my own sailboat, and an
    entirely unembarrassed amount of video games, series, and films (I think I might watch more in a weekend most people do in a month).
  </p>
  <p>
    Looking for the résumé? That one lives on
    <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/davidlowelarsson/">LinkedIn</a>. This is the rest.
  </p>

  <section aria-labelledby="recent-heading">
    <h2 id="recent-heading" class="section-heading">Recent</h2>
    <PostList posts={recent} />
    <p class="all-posts"><a href="/posts/">All posts →</a></p>
  </section>
</Base>
